# Setup Guide for C++ Program with OpenCV

This guide walks you through the setup required to compile and run the C++ program using OpenCV. Instructions are provided for macOS, Windows, and Linux.


## Prerequisites

C++ Compiler: Ensure you have a C++ compiler that supports at least C++17 (e.g., g++ or clang).
OpenCV Library: Install OpenCV 4 or later.
pkg-config (for macOS and Linux): Required for linking OpenCV.


## Setup Instructions by Operating System

## macOS

**Install Homebrew (if not already installed):**
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

**Install pkg-config and OpenCV:**
brew install pkg-config
brew install opencv

**Verify the OpenCV installation:**
pkg-config --modversion opencv4

**Compile the program:**
g++ -std=c++17 -o E1 E1.cpp `pkg-config --cflags --libs opencv4`
g++ -std=c++17 -o E2 E2.cpp `pkg-config --cflags --libs opencv4`
g++ -std=c++17 -o E3 E3.cpp `pkg-config --cflags --libs opencv4`

**Run the program:**
./E1
./E2
./E3


## Windows

**Install MinGW-w64 or a compatible compiler:**
Download and install from MinGW-w64.

**Install OpenCV:**
Download OpenCV from opencv.org.
Extract the archive and set the environment variable OpenCV_DIR to the folder containing the OpenCV libraries.

**Compile the program:** Replace <opencv_include_dir> and <opencv_library_dir> with the paths to OpenCV's include and lib directories.
g++ -std=c++17 -o E1 E1.cpp -I<opencv_include_dir> -L<opencv_library_dir> -lopencv_core -lopencv_imgproc -lopencv_highgui
g++ -std=c++17 -o E2 E2.cpp -I<opencv_include_dir> -L<opencv_library_dir> -lopencv_core -lopencv_imgproc -lopencv_highgui
g++ -std=c++17 -o E3 E3.cpp -I<opencv_include_dir> -L<opencv_library_dir> -lopencv_core -lopencv_imgproc -lopencv_highgui

**Run the program:**
E1.exe
E2.exe
E3.exe


## Linux

**Install the required tools:**
sudo apt update
sudo apt install build-essential pkg-config libopencv-dev

**Verify the OpenCV installation:**
pkg-config --modversion opencv4

**Compile the program:**
g++ -std=c++17 -o E1 E1.cpp `pkg-config --cflags --libs opencv4`
g++ -std=c++17 -o E2 E2.cpp `pkg-config --cflags --libs opencv4`
g++ -std=c++17 -o E3 E3.cpp `pkg-config --cflags --libs opencv4`

**Run the program:**
./E1
./E2
./E3